.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-3-7::.
House: colonial, victorian, craftsman, townhouse
The people use 4 different means of transport: airplane, ship, snowmobile, van
1. the person driving the van is on the right of the colonial house##1
2. the colonial house is on the far left or far right##3
3. the person driving the ship is on the left of the person driving the snowmobile##1
4. the craftsman house is between the victorian house and the townhouse house##2
5. the person driving the ship is the person driving the ship##1
6. the person driving the ship is between the person driving the snowmobile and the townhouse house##2

.:: Answer ::.
|               |    1     |  2   |   3    |     4      |
| House   | colonial | townhouse | craftsman | victorian     |
| Transport     | airplane | van  | ship   | snowmobile |

